  "text": "The Kafka consumer fetch request lifecycle involves multiple layers of request building, network communication, and record processing. Here's the complete end-to-end chain:\n\n**1. Consumer Poll Entry Point:**\nThe journey starts at `ClassicKafkaConsumer.poll()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java:624). This public API method calls the internal `poll(Timer)` method which orchestrates the entire fetching process.\n\n**2. Fetch Orchestration:**\n`ClassicKafkaConsumer.pollForFetches()` (line 690) coordinates the fetch cycle:\n- First attempts to collect already buffered fetches via `fetcher.collectFetch()`\n- If no buffered data, sends new fetch requests via `sendFetches()`\n- Performs network poll via `client.poll()` to receive responses\n- Collects returned fetch data again via `fetcher.collectFetch()`\n\n**3. Fetch Request Building:**\n`Fetcher.sendFetches()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetcher.java:105) initiates fetch request transmission. It delegates to `AbstractFetch.prepareFetchRequests()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:412) which:\n- Identifies fetchable partitions without buffered data\n- For each partition, creates `FetchRequest.PartitionData` objects with topic ID, fetch offset, fetch size, and leader epoch\n- Uses `FetchSessionHandler` to manage incremental fetch sessions\n- Builds fetch requests per broker node\n\n**4. FetchRequest Construction:**\nThe `FetchRequest` class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/FetchRequest.java:41) encapsulates the complete fetch request with partition-level metadata including offsets and sizing information.\n\n**5. Network Communication and Response Handling:**\nOnce requests are sent via `sendFetchesInternal()`, responses are processed by `AbstractFetch.handleFetchSuccess()` (line 150) which:\n- Extracts the `FetchResponse` from the network response\n- Uses `FetchSessionHandler` to validate and process the response\n- Parses response data via `FetchResponse.responseData()`\n- Creates `CompletedFetch` objects for each partition in the response\n- Adds them to the `FetchBuffer` for later consumption\n\n**6. Response Parsing:**\nThe `FetchResponse` class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/FetchResponse.java:53) provides utilities like `recordsOrFail()` to extract the raw `MemoryRecords` from `FetchResponseData.PartitionData`.\n\n**7. Record Collection and Deserialization:**\n`Fetcher.collectFetch()` (line 145) delegates to `FetchCollector.collectFetch()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/FetchCollector.java:92) which:\n- Iterates through completed fetches from the buffer\n- Calls `initialize()` to validate responses and prepare record iteration\n- For each partition, calls `CompletedFetch.fetchRecords()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CompletedFetch.java:252) which:\n  - Iterates through `RecordBatch` objects from the response\n  - For each record, calls `parseRecord()` (line 307) to deserialize key/value using configured deserializers\n  - Filters control records and aborted transactions\n  - Returns `List<ConsumerRecord<K, V>>`\n- Creates `Fetch<K, V>` objects containing the deserialized records and next offset metadata\n\n**8. ConsumerRecords Construction:**\nBack in `ClassicKafkaConsumer.poll()` (line 663), the final step constructs the public API return value:\n- Creates `new ConsumerRecords<>(fetch.records(), fetch.nextOffsets())`\n- `fetch.records()` is the `Map<TopicPartition, List<ConsumerRecord<K, V>>>` containing deserialized records\n- `fetch.nextOffsets()` is the `Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata>` for position tracking\n- Applies consumer interceptors before returning\n\n**9. ConsumerRecords API:**\nThe `ConsumerRecords` class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/ConsumerRecords.java:34) provides the public interface allowing users to iterate records by partition and access next committed offsets.\n\n**Key Supporting Infrastructure:**\n- `FetchBuffer` manages buffered completed fetches awaiting processing\n- `FetchCollector` orchestrates the conversion of network responses to consumer-visible records\n- `FetchConfig` encapsulates fetch configuration (batch size, max records, isolation level)\n- `FetchSessionHandler` optimizes fetch requests by managing incremental session state\n- `Deserializers` handle key/value deserialization at record parsing time"
}

